      <abstract>
        <label>Abstract</label>
        <sec sec-type="background">
          <title>Background</title>
          <p>The scarab beetle genera <italic><tp:taxon-name><tp:taxon-name-part taxon-name-part-type="genus">Orphnus</tp:taxon-name-part></tp:taxon-name></italic> Macleay and <italic><tp:taxon-name><tp:taxon-name-part taxon-name-part-type="genus">Delopleurus</tp:taxon-name-part></tp:taxon-name></italic> Boheman are most speciose in the Afrotropical region. However, a number of species are only known from type specimens, sometimes only from one sex.</p>
        </sec>
        <sec sec-type="new information">
          <title>New information</title>
          <p>New locality records of <italic><tp:taxon-name><tp:taxon-name-part taxon-name-part-type="genus">Orphnus</tp:taxon-name-part> <tp:taxon-name-part taxon-name-part-type="species">drumonti</tp:taxon-name-part></tp:taxon-name></italic> Frolov (<tp:taxon-name><tp:taxon-name-part taxon-name-part-type="subfamily">Orphninae</tp:taxon-name-part></tp:taxon-name>) and <italic><tp:taxon-name><tp:taxon-name-part taxon-name-part-type="genus">Delopleurus</tp:taxon-name-part> <tp:taxon-name-part taxon-name-part-type="species">naviauxi</tp:taxon-name-part></tp:taxon-name></italic> Frolov et Cambefort (<tp:taxon-name><tp:taxon-name-part taxon-name-part-type="subfamily">Scarabaeinae</tp:taxon-name-part></tp:taxon-name>) are given. The previously unknown female of the former and male of the latter species are described.</p>
        </sec>
